# Documentation Standards for Speedy Delivery

## README Structure
- Clear project description and purpose
- Installation instructions with prerequisites
- Usage examples with common scenarios
- Configuration options and customization
- Troubleshooting section with common issues
- Contributing guidelines reference

## Markdown Formatting
- Use headers for clear section organization
- Include code blocks with language specification
- Use emojis for visual appeal and quick scanning
- Implement proper link formatting
- Include badges for project status

## Installation Documentation
- Prerequisites clearly listed (macOS, fswatch)
- Step-by-step installation process
- Alternative installation methods
- Verification steps after installation
- Uninstallation instructions

## Usage Documentation
- Basic usage examples
- Advanced usage scenarios
- Command-line options and flags
- Configuration file locations
- Log file locations and debugging

## Contributing Guidelines
- Development setup instructions
- Code style guidelines
- Testing requirements
- Pull request process
- Issue reporting format

## Changelog Format
- Follow Keep a Changelog format
- Use semantic versioning
- Categorize changes (Added, Changed, Fixed, etc.)
- Include dates for releases
- Link to relevant issues/PRs
